  ]
)

=== poster
With #raw("poster(tiling, theme: default-theme)") the tiling gets applied to the whole page dimensions. An example usage could look like:
```typc
#set page(paper: "a2")
#set text(18pt)

#let tiling = /* define poster content and layout */

poster(tiling)
```

= Themes
Litfass supports the use of themes to style the content laid out by a tiling. Predefined themes can be imported from #raw("import litfass.themes: *"). As for now, one basic default theme is provided under #raw("litfass.themes.basic"). For this manual we used a modified version of the #raw("basic") theme:

#let inline-box = inline-box.with(theme: theme)
#let tiling = vs(
  cut: 50%,
  cbx(lorem(12), title: [foo]),
  hs(cut: 40%, cbx(lorem(5)), cbx(lorem(6), title: [bar]))
)

